              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Windowless hydrogen gas target. Target areal density",
                "was (6.9 +- 0.2)E+18 atoms/cm2 at 5.5 torr of H2"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The Daresbury Recoil Separator (DRS) has been",
                "used to separate the  recoils of interest from the",
                "unreacted primary beam. The main elements are  two",
                "Wien velocity filters. The system is appended with a",
                "magnetic dipole and  three quadrupole triplets to",
                "focus selected reaction product onto focal  plane."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Selected ions were identified in focal plane",
                "with a segmented,  isobutane filled gas ionization",
                "counter"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "OLMS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Mass separation of reaction products by two",
                "Wien filters was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
